    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>英語で:</strong> Amongst the mountains and cities, Japanese farmers still manage to find land to grow their produce. Around 12% of land is used for agriculture, mostly for growing rice, but also for wheat, barley, sweet potatoes and vegetables.</p>

